self.title: CDISC SEND Pregnancy Findings Test Name Terminology

definition: Terminology for the test names relevant to pregnancy.
name: Pregnancy Findings Test Name
preferredTerm: CDISC SEND Pregnancy Findings Test Name Terminology

terms.definition: A measurement of the average weight of all live female fetuses.
A measurement of the average weight of all live fetuses.
A measurement of the average weight of all live male fetuses.
The number of corpora lutea present in the ovary/ovaries.
A measurement (expressed as a fraction or percent) of the number of live female fetuses to the total number of live male and female fetuses.
A measurement (expressed as a fraction or percent) of the number of live male fetuses to the total number of live male and female fetuses.
A measurement of the number of dead fetuses in the uterus/uterine horn(s).
A measurement of the number of early resorptions in the uterus/uterine horn(s).
A measurement of the total number of fetuses (alive plus dead) present in the uterus/uterine horn(s).
A measurement of the number of implantations in the uterus/uterine horn(s).
A measurement of the total number of deaths (dead fetuses plus resorptions) in the uterus/uterine horn(s).
A measurement of the number of late resorptions in the uterus/uterine horn(s).
A measurement of the number of live female fetuses present in the uterus/uterine horn(s).
A measurement of the number of live fetuses in the uterus/uterine horn(s).
A measurement of the number of live male fetuses present in the uterus/uterine horn(s).
A measurement of the total number of resorptions (early plus late) in the uterus/uterine horn(s).
"The percentage of implants that died, calculated as the number of intrauterine deaths divided by the number of implantations and multiplied by 100."
"The percentage of released ova that failed to implant, calculated as the number of corpora lutea minus the number of implantations, divided by the number of corpora lutea and multiplied by 100."
The condition or state of the subject with regards to pregnancy.
A measurement of the total weight of all live fetuses.
